title: Waiting for Gumball: Telly
description: Grady thinks the TV show they are watching is awful and decides to get the gang together to make their own show.

title: Clayton
description: Darwin needs to find a photo of Clayton to put on the cover of the school yearbook - but he makes the mistake of seeking help from Tobias, who has his eye on the cover spot himself! Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The Kiss
description: Gumball is traumatised when accidentally kissed on the mouth by his Grandma JoJo.

title: The Shell
description: Gumball inadvertently cracks open Penny's shell and discovers who she really is inside . . . While performing a school play, Gumball is so nervous about kissing Penny that he accidentally headbutts her and cracks open her shell. They discover that under Penny's shell is an emotional shape-shifting inner self. Penny's father is determined for Penny to keep it hidden but Gumball encourages her to show the world who, or what, she really is . . .

title: Waiting for Gumball: Weird Food
description: Puppet Gumball imagines some weird food then tries it.

title: The Heart
description: When Mr. Robinson accidentally let slip how little he cares for Gumball and Darwin, they react by giving him the cold shoulder.  Surprisingly Mr. Robinson misses them and tries to win back their friendship. After a few failed attempts, Gumball and Darwin realize that Mr. Robinson's heart is protecting him, so they give it an intense affection overload.

title: Sarah
description: Darwin asks Sarah for a photo to put on the cover of the school yearbook. But when Sarah tries to help, things get a little sticky. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Teachers
description: When Darwin asks his friends which teacher deserves to be on the yearbook cover, they struggle to find a single worthy candidate! Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The Decisions
description: When everything goes wrong in Darwin's life, he begins to suspect that Gumball's bad influence might be to blame. Darwin decides to go elsewhere for guidance and finds a new mentor in Alan. But maybe it's time Darwin started making his own decisions.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Spoons
description: Frank has taken Grady's beloved house Spoon. Grady is forced into a dance off to win it back.

title: Alan
description: Darwin wants to put Alan on the cover of the school yearbook - but Alan's apparent modesty gets in the way. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Banana Joe
description: When Principal Brown sets Darwin the task of making the school yearbook, Darwin starts by asking class clown Banana Joe for a simple selfie to put on the cover. But with Banana Joe, things are never that simple. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Pineapple
description: Gumball briefly loses his puppet mouth to an enthusiastic Pineapple.

title: Waiting for Gumball: BirdPlaneBird
description: Darwin and BirdPlaneBird try to share a refreshing drink, it turns out to be hard as a puppet.

title: The Misunderstandings
description: Gumball has misunderstood about his date with Penny. He thought they were meeting for dinner but they were actually meeting for lunch at a Diner called Dinner. He runs to the mall but everyone he meets on the way seems to misunderstand him in a different way. Once he finally does get to the mall, it seems all his misunderstandings have caught up with him.

title: The Love
description: The residents of Elmore search for the meaning of love.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Insulting Voices
description: Gumball and Darwin play with smaller hand puppets of themselves who mimic their voices very badly.

title: The Wish
description: Gumball and Darwin panic when they suspect they've accidentally turned Miss Simian into a cushion, by wishing upon an enchanted key ring. Surely the only way to break the curse is a confession of true love from Principal Brown. Simple!

title: The Matchmaker
description: Gumball catches Darwin gazing wistfully at a photo of Teri on Elmore Plus and secretly enlists Carrie to help bring them together. But when they can't make Darwin and Teri's love blossom naturally, they decide to make it happen supernaturally.

title: The Watch
description: Gumball and Darwin learn that getting a family heirloom back off an old man is harder than you might think.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Infinite Loop
description: Gumball and Darwin discover smaller hand puppet  versions of themselves and get caught in an infinite loop of puppets.

title: The Date
description: Gumball discovers the difference between a "date" and a "pet's funeral"...the hard way.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Clean
description: Grady is determined to tidy up the house and persuades Howdy and Frank to help. While cleaning Frank unexpectedly discovers the love of his life under a bin bag.

title: The Void
description: When Gumball and Darwin investigate a missing classmate, they discover a far greater mystery . . . about Elmore. Gumball and Darwin start noticing small details around Elmore High that don't add up. They come to the conclusion that Molly has disappeared, even though nobody else remembers her ever having existed. Mr Small confirms their suspicions and tells them that things are not always what they seem in Elmore. They set off on a quest to rescue Molly in an alternate dimension, and soon need rescuing themselves!

title: Waiting for Gumball: Cool to Be Felt
description: Gumball and Darwin realize they are puppets and it's seriously cool.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Bored
description: Frank is bored and pesters the others to entertain him for the afternoon.

title: The Web
description: Gumball and Darwin realize that the adult residents of Elmore are dangerously naive when it comes to being safe online. In fact they are in serious need of the boys help with even the simplest of tasks. And no more so than their mom, Nicole.

title: Carrie
description: Darwin sets out to find a photo of Carrie for the cover of the school yearbook - but they end up reminiscing about all their past spooky shenanigans. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The Wicked
description: Gumball and Darwin try to find a single nice quality about their neighbor, Mrs Robinson.

title: The Romantic
description: After Gumball convinces himself that Penny doesn't love him as much as she used to, he decides to put together a romantic quest to remind her of all the good times they've had together. But Gumball's romantic gesture backfires, landing Penny and maybe their relationship in serious peril.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Gnomes
description: Gumball and Darwin realize that anything they imagine will become real in Puppet World, but all they can think of are Garden Gnomes.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Beards
description: Puppet Gumball and Darwin discover they can grow very weird beards.

title: The Wand
description: Gumball and Darwin make their dad believe in magic again.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Grump
description: Frank is getting grumpy waiting for Gumball and Darwin to return so Grady and Howdy throw a party to cheer him up.
